cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using Convolutional Neural Networks for image segmentation of lake ice from webcam images. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper mentions scraping images from photo-sharing websites. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a state-of-the-art CNN model for semantic image segmentation. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is relevant as the paper deals with image analysis and segmentation. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with webcam images and crowd-sourced images.
